12/08/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Greek and NATO planes launched continuous patrols of the skies Wednesday (11 August), two days ahead of the official opening of the Summer Olympics in Athens. 
The security umbrella includes Greek Mirage jetfighters as well as NATO AWACS aircraft. 
Earlier this year, the Greek government asked for NATO's assistance.
In other news Wednesday, former US President George Bush, the head of the US delegation to the Games, expressed confidence in Greece's security plans. 
Bush is attending the Games with his wife Barbara and granddaughters Barbara and Jenna. 
(NATO Web site, Kathimerini, AP - 11/08/04)
